quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,10,"He it is who sendeth down from the heaven water for you, wherefrom is drinking and wherefrom are trees whereas ye pasture your herds"
  16,11,He groweth for you thereby the corn and olives and date- palms and grapes and all kinds of fruit. Verily therein is a sign for a people who ponder
  16,12,"And He hath subiected for you the night and the day and the sun and the moon, and the stars are subjected by His command. Verily therein are signs for a people who understand"
  16,13,And He hath subjected for you whatsoever He hath multiplied for you on the earth of various kinds. Verily therein is a sign for a people who receive admonition
  16,14,"And He it is who hath subjected the sea that ye may eat thereout flesh fresh and bring forth therefrom ornaments that ye wear. And thou beholdest ships ploughing therein, and it is in order that ye may seek of His grace, and that haply ye may give thanks"
  16,15,"And He hath cast on the earth firm mountains lest it move away with you, and rivers and paths that haply ye may be directed"
  16,16,And also landmarks; and by the stars they are guided
  16,17,Is there one who createth like unto one who createth not? Will ye not then be admonished
  16,18,"And if ye would count the favours of Allah ye could not compute them verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  16,19,And Allah knoweth that which ye keep secret and that which ye publish
  16,20,"And those upon whom they call beside Allahls have not created aught, and are themselves created"
  16,21,"Dead are they, not alive; and they perceive not when they will be raised up"